texts.text: *Sniff*
I smell humans... Where... Where are they...?
Crap... They're getting close...
It's only a matter of time until they find me.
*Groan*
No, don't wake up now... You're just gonna scream again when you see me.
The hell am I supposed to do...?
In here!

*Scream*
They found me!!
Hey, over here! A girl!
Koppa Tengu... You...
W-What? Nekomata? And humans? What about the others?
We got rid of them! But more importantly!
You! Do you know just exactly what you've done?!
Everyone, and master, are all dealing with this mess, and you even put Saki in harm's way!!
>Nekomata continues to berate Koppa Tengu...
Wow... Nekomata... She's really pissed off...
Anyways, Rika! Is that girl okay?
Yes. It looks like she just passed out.
Thank god...
Saki. Saki?

*Groan*
What's going...?
She's awake? Are you hurt anywhere?
No...
That's good. You... You seem to have gotten lost.
Lost... I think I was being chased by a monster too...
T-that was probably just a bad dream!
We're here so you're safe now!
...Wait, Miya! My cat, Miya...
*Meow*
Miya!
Thank you so much. You found Miya too!
*Meow*
>The girl squats down to pet her cat.
Hey, newbie... Is that?
>You nod and show her.
She really looks like a cat... Or she really is a cat.
I believe that's mission accomplished then.
Yeah, awesome!
>A shadow lurks behind the girl...!
*Roar*
Stragglers?! We're too...
*Hiss*

*Howl*
*Whimper*
>The demons vanish...
Just what did you plan on doing to her with me right here...?!
Uh oh...!
Huh? Are you...?
C-Crap...!!
N-No... I mean, this is...!
*Wince*
Wait! Miya!
You're Miya, right? Don't run.
...You weren't just a regular cat?
I-I'm sorry! Please don't be scared!
But I guess you should be scared... I can't think you'd want me as your...
Anyways. You won't see me again...
So again, I'm sorry...
Why are you saying that...?
I knew you weren't normal for a long time!
What?
You lived way longer than any cat I can think of,
and even started thinking that you might not be a cat at all.
Mom and dad said they thought the same thing.
But Miya, you're still family no matter what.
We waited until you decided that you wanted to talk and left you alone as a cat until then.
That's what we agreed on... But I don't want you to go.
Miya, if you say that you're gonna leave because now we know,
then we'll just keep pretending that you're a cat. So please don't leave us like this.
I mean, Miya... Aren't you supposed to be my big sister?
Saki...
...But. Can't you see I'm a demon?
I'm not any different from the monsters you're scared of.
You'd be okay with that?
Then I'll learn to not be so scared...
I want to know more about you too, Miya.
Ha, fine then. But don't come crawling to me if you start losing sleep over this.
Then we'll just have to sleep in the same bed!
>Nekomata and the girl hold hands as tears roll down from their eyes...
>A few days later...
Oh, those demons? They were all sealed back up.
My master wanted me to express his gratitude for what you did.
I see. I'm just glad everything could be resolved.
But is it really okay for me to be here? We're not really friends or anything...
It's fine. The boss said it's okay too.
Has anything changed for you since then?
Oh, yeah... I'm staying as a cat most of the time.
Yeah. She never lets me see her Nekomata form even when it's just the two of us.
Hiya, Saki! What's up?
Hi, Ririn!
Wait, how did you get in here?
I was let in after I saw one of you downstairs.
I let her in.
I let her in.
We're friends so...
You... Why...?
Yayâ™ª
But the fact that you're here means...
I thought you were back at the mountain...
And Kurama Tengu said that you're here so...
W-Wait, you're telling me you went up there alone?!
Yeah.
That's nowhere for a girl to go by herself!
I hope you didn't already forget what happened to you up there?!
But Kurama Tengu said all the bad monsters were gone...
You know Kurama Tengu is a "monster" too, right...?
Oni and Yaksini too? And Koppa Tengu?
All of them! Wait, you know the others too...?!
You're so overprotective, Miya! They're all good people... Or demons I guess?
There's no good or bad when it comes to demons! You're getting in way over your head!
Awww... But...
>Nekomata and her sister keep on arguing...
They seem happy don't they, Ririn?
Right? And they're really acting like sisters too.
I guess people get along when they find the right match.
So maybe humans and demons are the same way...
...To be fair, I think that had to be pretty rare.
Those two are the exception to the rule.
An overwhelming majority probably don't get along.
But I'm glad this worked out.
At least we know it's possible now for us to get along with others, even if they're not human.
